Ranger Help for: equipment
==========================

SUMMARY:
Rangers favor practical equipment suited to life in the wilderness.
Leather and studded leather armors are preferred, as heavier plate
armors restrict the stealth and agility a Ranger depends on. Chainmail
is acceptable but somewhat noisy.

The defining weapon of a Ranger is the bow. Rangers can carve their own
bows and arrows from harvested wood, creating reliable weapons from the
land itself. Medium swords, daggers, and staves round out the Ranger's
arsenal. Rangers are also able to craft torches, rope, tents, and
fish traps from natural materials gathered in the wild.

Rangers can balance weapons to improve accuracy, and treat leather
armor to improve its protection. A well-equipped Ranger carries a
quiver for arrows, a carved bow, and whatever tools the terrain demands.

